<span class="section_title">2008 INTERNATIONAL CES ISSUES CALL FOR CONFERENCE SPEAKERS</span>

	<br><br>
	<span class="subhead">Deadline for Speaker Applications Set for July 13, 2007</span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;6/19/2007</i></strong>
<br><br>
The International CES<sup>&#174</sup>, the 

world&rsquo;s largest  consumer technology tradeshow, has issued its &ldquo;Call for Speaker&rdquo; applications  for the 

2008 International CES, which will run January 7-10, 2008, in Las Vegas, Nevada.&nbsp; </p>
<p>With more than 175  sessions planned, the International CES conference program unites the  industry&rsquo;s most respected 

authorities and educates attendees on the newest  trends, strategies and profit opportunities emerging in consumer 

technology.  More than 140,000 attendees including content and wireless developers, corporate  buyers and retailers, consumer 

technology manufacturers, media, analysts and  venture capitalists, from 140 countries attend the International CES. Notable  

industry experts share advice and knowledge throughout the CES conference  program.</p>

Speaker proposals  are due by July 13, 2007. Proposals can be submitted online at <em><a 

href="http://www.CESweb.org/attendees/conferences/default.asp" 

target="_blank">www.CESweb.org/attendees/conferences/default.asp</a></em>.</p>
  <p>Topics for the 2008 International CES conference  program include: </p>
  <table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="708">
